Description:
Prerequisite:

  • ‘Read&Write’ or at least ‘Read’ permission for the folder is required to view the folder and the documents in it.

Prerequisite:

  • Folder creation permission is needed.
  • ‘Read&Write’ access for the folder

History: Completing Pull Request 55 and the associated work items.
Description:
Prerequisite:

  • Dropdown field attributes configuration permission is needed.

Title: Feature ID: SUB006 - Uploading a document
History: Completing Pull Request 55 and the associated work items.
Description:
Prerequisite:

  • Document upload permission is needed.

Title: Feature ID: SUB007 - Approval flow for new and revised document uploading process
History: Completing Pull Request 55 and the associated work items.
Description:
Prerequisite:

  • Document approval – Approve/Reject a document permission is needed.
  • Read&Write access to the folder  is needed

Title: Feature ID: SUB008 - Awaiting approval
History: Completing Pull Request 55 and the associated work items.
Description:
Prerequisite:

  • Document approval – Approve/Reject a document permission is needed.

Title: Feature ID: SUB009 - Status – Documents submitted for approval
History: Completing Pull Request 55 and the associated work items.
Description:
Prerequisite:

  •  ‘Document upload’ or ‘Document revision’ permission is needed.

Title: Feature ID: SUB010 - Edit – Uploading revised version of a document
History: Completing Pull Request 55 and the associated work items.
Description:
Prerequisite:

  • Document revision permission is needed.

Title: Feature ID: SUB011 - Document versioning
Feature ID: SUB012 - Email notification
Feature ID: SUB013 - Search
Feature ID: SUB014 - Advanced search – Document section
Feature ID: SUB015 - Deleting a folder/document
Description:
Prerequisite:

  • Delete document/folder permission is needed.
  • Read&Write permission for the documents/folders which the user is trying to delete.

Title: Feature ID: SUB016 - Trash folder
Description:
Prerequisite:

  • Delete document/folder permission is needed.
  • ‘Read&Write’ permission for the folder is needed. That is, user can able to see the documents/files deleted from the folders for which he/she has ‘Read&Write’ permission. By that way, the user can see the files and also restore it if required.

Title: Feature ID: SUB017 -Document expiry
Description:
Prerequisite:

  • To set the document expiry date, user needs ‘Document upload’ permission.

Title: Feature ID: SUB018 - Reports
Description:
Prerequisite:

  •  ‘Reports’ permission is needed.

Title: SUB001: Sample List
Description:
1.       Sample list can be accessed by any Plant users / Agro Lab users / Admin with the application web URL without logging into the application.

2.       Sample list page lists Starch samples and EM/Miscellaneous samples in a separate tab. Display order should be, recently barcode generated being first on the list.

    1. Starch sample tab:
      1.  Displays the list of Starch sample details for which the barcode code was generated.
      2. The total number of Starch sample details should be displayed next to the tab name as shown in the wireframe.
    2. EM / Misc sample tab:
      1.  Displays the list of EM / Miscellaneous sample details for which the barcode code was generated.
      2. The total number of EM / Miscellaneous sample details should be displayed next to the tab name as shown in the wireframe.

3.       A single page to display up to 10 samples.

4.       Each tab should have the pagination to navigate to other list of samples.

5.       Each sample in the list view to display the following details as shown in the wireframe Fig: 1,2

Details

Description

Plant Name

Plant Name as a part of Sample submission.

Batch Number (only for Starch sample)

Batch Number as a part of Sample submission.

PIN Code (only for Starch sample)

PIN code as a part of Sample submission.

Sample ID (only for EM/Misc sample)

Sample ID as a part of Sample submission.

Generated Date & Time

System Date & Time when the barcode was generated.

PIN Code (only for Starch sample)

PIN Code as a part of Sample submission.

Test List

An icon is displayed in each row as displayed in the wireframe.

On click of the icon, a pop is displayed in which a list of tests for the particular sample are displayed as shown in the wireframe.

 

6.       User can search for a sample using the Search option.

    1. Samples can be searched by selecting column name in which the search should be initiated.
    2. Columns that should be involved in the search are,
      1. Plant Name
      2. Batch Number (only for Starch sample)
      3. PIN Code (only for Starch sample)
      4. Sample ID (only for EM/Misc sample)
      5. All – User can search from all the above-mentioned fields when he/she is unsure of where the search should be initiated.

7.       On clicking a particular rectangle tab/row, user is navigated to the “Sample Details” page for the particular sample.

8.       On click of “+” symbol in the Sidenav menu, user will be navigated to the “Sample Submission” page.

9.       On click of “Login icon”, user will be navigated to Azure AD login page.

Title: SUB003: Sample Submission
Description:
1. Any Plant user can access the Sample Submission page.
  2. On click of “Sample List” link (breadcrumb), user is navigated back to the “Sample List” page (Fig: 1).
  3. Sample submission page consists of the following fields:

 

 

Sl. No

Label/Key

Value - the field must accept

1

 

Plant Name

- Mandatory Field
- Supports Alphanumeric and Special characters
- Maximum field length is up to 100 characters

2

 

First Name

- Mandatory Field
- Supports only alphabets.

- Maximum field length is up to 100 characters

3

 

Last Name

- Mandatory Field
- Supports only Alphabets.

- Maximum field length is up to 100 characters

4

 

Email ID

- Non - Mandatory Field
- Supports Alphanumeric and Special characters

- Maximum field length is up to 100 characters

   ex: test@test.com

5

 

Type of Sample

- Mandatory Field

 

- On select of “Starch sample” button - “Batch number” and “PIN code” input field should be displayed.

 

  1. Batch Number:

         a. Mandatory field.

         b. Supports Alphanumeric characters.

         c. Maximum number of characters is 20 characters.

 

   2. PIN code:

         a. Mandatory field.

         b. Supports Alphanumeric characters and special characters.

         c. Maximum number of characters is 20 characters.

         d. If the user enters PIN code which does not exist in active Micro Manifest – An error message “Please enter valid PIN Code” is displayed.

 

- On select of “EM / Miscellaneous sample” button - “Description” and “Tests to be performed” input fields are displayed.

 

1.       Sample ID:

  1. Mandatory field.
  2. Supports alphanumeric and special characters.
  3. Maximum number of characters is 20 characters.

     

2.       Description:

         a. Non-Mandatory field.

         b. Supports Alphanumeric and special characters.

         c. Maximum number of characters is 500 characters.

 

        3. Test to be performed:

         a. Mandatory field.

         b. Supports only Alphanumeric and special characters.

         c. Maximum number of characters is 50 characters.

         d. On click of “+” icon next to the “Test” input field, a new Test input field needs to         be created along with “-” and “+ “icons as shown in the wireframe.

            1. User can add maximum of 20 Test input fields.

      b. On click of “-” icon next to the “Test” input field, the respective Test input field needs to be deleted.

6

Reset button

On click of Reset button, the data entered in the input fields should be reset.

6

 

Submit button

- On click of Submit button, a barcode needs to be generated along with Batch number & PIN Code information (for Starch sample) and Sample ID information (for EM/Miscellaneous sample).

- User is navigated to Sample Summary page.

- Details are added to the Sample List page.

 

Note: Plant Name, First Name, Last name, Email ID fields are auto-complete fields.

Title: SUB007: Micro Manifest upload
Description:
1. Upon login and on click of “Micro Manifest” option in the Sidenav menu, user will be navigated to Micro Manifest upload screen.
  2. On click of “Download template” link, user can download the Micro manifest template (sample document) which is in CSV format.
  3. On click of “Upload” button, user can upload the Micro manifest file only if the file is in CSV format.
    1. Name of the file uploaded is displayed in the text field.
    2. Success message “<File name> uploaded Successfully” is displayed as shown in the wireframe when the file is uploaded successfully without any errors.
    3. An error message “File upload failed. Please upload CSV file” is displayed when the uploaded file is of different format other than CSV.
    4. If the data entered in the Micro Manifest doesn’t match with the Micro Manifest template – An error message “Failed to upload <File name>, kindly download the file to view errors” is displayed.
      1. On click of “download”, user can download the Micro Manifest file which was uploaded along with the error messages.
  4. On click of “Recent upload” tab, user can view the list of Micro Manifest that are uploaded.
    1. Display order should be, recently uploaded Micro Manifest being first on the list.
  5. Each Micro Manifest in the list view to display the following details as shown in the wireframe

 

 

Details

Description

File Name

File Name as a part of Micro Manifest upload.

Uploaded by

Name of user based on login.

Uploaded date and time

Date and time when the Micro Manifest was uploaded.

Download icon

On click of download icon, user can download the particular Micro Manifest.

Title: SUB008: Dashboard
Description:
1. Upon login, Admin and Agro Lab users has the ability to see the dashboard with following reports:
    1. Number of Barcode generated:
      1. Displays name of Samples – Starch sample and EM/Misc sample on the x-axis.
      2. Displays the count of Starch sample and EM/Misc samples for which the barcode was generated by the plant users based on the filter on y - axis.

         
    2. Number of Barcode scanned:
      1. Displays name of Samples - Starch sample and EM/Misc sample on the x-axis.
      2. Displays the count of Starch sample and EM/Misc samples scanned by the lab users based on the filter on y - axis.

Title: SUB009: Authentication and Authorisation
Description:
1.       Quality Track and Trace web application will be integrated with Ingredion’s active directory for the authentication and authorization.

2.       Whenever a user wanted to login, he/she will be redirected to the AD page and upon successful authentication and authorization comes backs to the application.

3.       All the role definition and user access are defined at Ingredion AD level.

Title: SUB0011: Print functionality (CR)
Description:
1. In Sample List page for both Starch/EM sample, Date picker option will be displayed as shown in the wire-frame.
    1. "Select date" will be displayed as a place holder.
    2. On click of input field, a calendar will be displayed.
    3. On selecting a date, date will be displayed in "Month name DD, YYYY" format ex: "Feb 20, 2020" and the Sample details will be displayed based on the selected date, same information will be sent to the print.
  2. Print button will be displayed as disabled at the beginning until a date is selected.
    1. On selecting a date, the Print button will be enabled.
    2. On click of the Print button, the user is navigated to the browser print preview page.
  3. Print preview is displayed in a tabular format with Plant Name, Batch Number, PIN Code, Generated Date & Time and Test list for Starch sample and Plant Name, Sample ID, Generated Date & Time and Test list for EM sample as shown in the wireframe.

Title: CR3: Product icon configuration
Description:
1. Folder which consists of Icons can be uploaded in Product icons field in URL paths tab.
  2. If uploaded images are not in svg format, display "Please upload svg icons" is displayed.
  3. When new products are added to the system, a unique icon (which is not assigned to any the other products before) is assigned to the new products.
  4. Admin can change the icon assigned to a product using the below screen.
    1. Icon configuration tab is displayed in Configure page.
      1. A drop down is displayed which consists of the Product name which are uploaded to the system along with the icon.
      2. Search option is present in the dropdown as shown in the wireframe to search a specific product name.
      3. User can select the Product name for which the icon should be re-assigned from the dropdown.
        1. On selecting the product, the product name and the symbol assigned to it is displayed in the input field as shown in the wireframe.
      4. A set of un-assigned icons (icons which are not assigned to any other products) are displayed at the right side as shown in the wireframe.
      5. On click of the icon in the icon section, the selected icon is highlighted as shown in the wireframe.
      6. Apply button will be disabled at the beginning, it will be enabled only when both Product name and product symbol are selected as shown in the wireframe.
        1. On click of Apply button, the selected icon is applied for the Product which is selected in the drop down field.
        2. The icon which was assigned for the Product before will be part of un-assigned icons and will be displayed in the set of un-assigned icons.
  5. Scenario: When there are no icons in the system and if new products are added to the system, then a default icon will be assigned to the new products.
  6. Note: The products which are assigned with a default icon will be assigned with a new icon only if the Admin assigns a new icon or when the icon’s name is same as Product name.

Title: Print "Test name" in individual labels for both Starch & EM sample
Description:
1. Once the user logs in as Lab user and then scans the barcode or when the user logs in as Lab user and then clicks on any of the row in Sample Details screen, user is navigated to "Sample details" screen, when the user clicks on "Print" button in Sample Details screen:
    1. For Starch sample - Each "Test name" needs to be printed in different labels along with "Batch Number" and "PIN code".
      1. example: If "Batch Number" - "123" with "PIN code" - "100" has "5" tests then, 5 tests needs to be printed in 5 different labels.
        1. "Batch Number - 123", PIN code - 100, "Test Name 1" should be printed in "Label 1".
        2. "Batch Number - 123", PIN code - 100, "Test Name 2" should be printed in "Label 2"
        3. "Batch Number - 123", PIN code - 100, "Test Name 3" should be printed in "Label 3".
        4. "Batch Number - 123", PIN code - 100, "Test Name 4" should be printed in "Label 4"
        5. "Batch Number - 123", PIN code - 100, "Test Name 5" should be printed in "Label 5"
    2. For EM ​sample - Each "Test name" needs to be printed in different labels along with "Sample ID".
      1. example: If "Sample ID" - "123" has "5" tests then, 5 tests needs to be printed in 5 different labels.
        1. "Sample ID - 123", "Test Name 1" should be printed in "Label 1".
        2. "Sample ID - 123", "Test Name 2" should be printed in "Label 2"
        3. "Sample ID - 123", "Test Name 3" should be printed in "Label 3".
        4. "Sample ID - 123", "Test Name 4" should be printed in "Label 4"
        5. "Sample ID", "Test Name 5" should be printed in "Label 5"
  2. Note: The label dimension is changed to "308*102" pixels.
    1. Font size of the text is changed to 10 pixels.

Title: CR 1 : DMS - Provision to view some of the files within the application
Description:
DMS application should have the provision to view the following files within the application when its doubled clicked.
  • PDF
  • Word
  • Excel
  • PPT
  • JPG
  • JPEG
  • PNG

Title: Ability to view the PDF files within DMS application
Description:
• DMS application should have the provision to display the PDF format files within the application when the particular file type is being double-clicked.
  • The pdf file should be displayed on a new page within the application with the breadcrumb and side navigation bar as it already exists.
    • User can navigate back to the folder using the breadcrumb
  • On the display page, the user should be given an option to download the file/document. Users can see the download icon on the top right-hand side corner.

Title: Displaying the user names of a user group in Access control - step 4
Average value and Standard deviation value round off logic
Description:
1. The Average Viscosity value and Standard deviation values for the Effect of Process Shear & Effect of Concentration need to be rounded off to 2 decimal values.
  2. Round off logic:
    1. If the next decimal value is 5 or more than 5 then the previous value should be rounded off to the next value.
      1. example: If the decimal value is 0.1287 then the rounded off value should be 0.13.
    2. If the next decimal value is less than 5 then the previous value should be the same value.
      1. example: If the decimal value is 0.1237 then the rounded off value should be 0.12.
  3. Please find the attachment for more details.
  4. Please find the below explanation that was shared by client.
  5. (The convention for rounding numbers is as follows: any calculated average viscosity or standard deviation value with X.XX50 and higher is rounded Up, whereas any number with X.XX49 and lower is rounded Down (X = any number).  The data table below is an example of only NOVATION PRIMA 300 at 25^s-1 on the Effect of Process Shear dashboard.  )

Title: Displaying the value for Cook Quality rating in tooltip and color of data point in Effect of Process Shear and Effect of Concentration
Description:
1. The Cook Quality Rating value displayed in the tooltip for Effect of Process Shear and Effect of Concentration needs to be pulled from the Process Tolerance SCQ Rating column of SCQFinalPr1 sheet.
  2. But the colors of the data points depend on values from the Cook Quality Rating column.
  3. The color code remains the same as shared before
  4. Uncooked ( for value 0)        - White (242, 242, 242)
    Under Cooked (for value 1) - Light Blue (185, 222, 255)
    Slightly Under Cooked ( for value 2) - Light Blue (114, 189, 255)
    Good Cook (for value 3)      - Blue (44, 156, 255)
    Slightly Over Cooked ( for value 4) - Dark Blue (0, 63, 118)
    Over Cooked (for value 5)   - Dark Grey (57, 57, 59)
    Sheared  (for value 6 and above)         - Black (0, 0, 0)
    For values which has two number (example: 2,3 or 5.7) - Purple  (112,48,160)

Title: Export to Excel
History: Completing Pull Request 961 and the associated work items.
Description:
1. There is change in Print button style.
  2. Initially both Print and Download button will be disabled.
  3. Once the user selects the date from the date picker, both Print and Download button will be enabled.

  6. File name: “Starch sample details – Date selected” or “EM / Misc details – Date selected”.
    1. Column headers will be in bold.
    2. Test names will be separated by commas in Test List column.
  7. Please refer to the attachments for the excel sheet format.
